# E2E Test Project DTOs

## Isolation from SUT

- **Declare DTOs in the E2E project only.** Do not import request/response DTOs from the Application or WebApi (SUT) projects.
- Place DTOs under `E2eBooking.WebApi.E2eTests/Shared/Dtos/`, grouped by feature (e.g. `Shared/Dtos/Bookings/`).
- Endpoints and tests should reference these local DTOs so the E2E suite stays independent of SUT internals.

## Nullable properties

- E2E DTOs should **generally use nullable properties** (e.g. `int?`, `DateTime?`, `string?`) so tests can omit or partially set payloads and assert API validation/behavior.

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD – DTO in E2E project with nullable properties
namespace E2eBooking.WebApi.E2eTests.Shared.Dtos.Bookings;

public record CreateBookingRequestDto
{
    public int? AiCustomerId { get; set; }
    public int? HumanResourceId { get; set; }
    public DateTime? Start { get; set; }
    public DateTime? End { get; set; }
}
```

```csharp
// ❌ BAD – importing SUT DTO
using E2eBooking.Application.Bookings.Dtos;
```

```csharp
// ❌ BAD – non-nullable only when partial payloads are needed
public int AiCustomerId { get; set; }
public DateTime Start { get; set; }
```
